1.content: Adolion is a large fantasy world. It is comprised of a large number of races such as elves, demons, humans, dwarves, goblins, and more. It has medieval technology, magic, and monsters.

10.content: Nagora Jungle - or the Vile Jungle - is a large jungle that covers 1/4th of Sebela. Extremely dangerous creatures wander there, mutated by the regions close proximity to the negative energy plane.

100.content: Chester Thornwick is a high-ranking nobleman in the Darran Kingdom who abused his authority to coordinate with Dark Elves to kidnap people to work in his brothels.

101.content: Shiya Mordered is a Half-demon succubus. Tsundere, haughty, dependable, arrogant, eloquent, charming, self-conscious, exaggerated. Best friends with Leila. Silver-blonde twintail hairstyle, red eyes, hourglass figure, maid outfit.

102.content: Reiner Dalmea is an Elf Butler, blue hair in a ponytail, Bubbly, eloquent, dynamic, enthusiastic, gullible, flippant, flamboyant. Acquaintances with Karos.

103.content: Glasnoa is a forest village. Primarily inhabited by elves. High Inquisition presence. Extremely far from Aegis City Closest Escape routes: Malert Mines, Scyldforst, Wyrdfang Peaks.

104.content: Malert Mines is an sprawling underground mine system that runs into the Darklands. Dwarvish, crumbling, high demonic presence, infested with demons, underground, lit by magic braziers, massive stone structures. Easy to hide in but easy to get lost. Leads to Darklands or near Aegis City.

105.content: Scyldforst is a large forest with deadly creatures inside. Forest canopy, very little light, fae creatures, deadly animals, dinosaurs, aggressive plant life, druids, maze-like. Most dangerous route to Aegis City. Leads to the human town of Carrion Hill.

106.content: Wyrdfang Peaks is a large snowy mountain range. Frost-covered mountains, extreme cold, yeti's, giantfolk, aggressive wolf-folk beastkin. Most direct route to Aegis City. Easy to die due to extreme temperature.

107.content: Selena Forestsong is a Half-demon succubi. Long blue hair, demon horns, dress, hourglass figure, red eyes, Demure, Insecure, bully victim, perceptive, kind. Wild Magic user.

108.content: A quest was posted by someone who wanted to rescue Selena. The pay is absurdly good and all that is required is to bring her to the Adventurer's Guild in Aegis City.

109.content: The Moonlight Blade Style is a style of fighting that uses a longsword and incorporates the half-swording style along with a variety of kicks, punches, and bashes. Its ultimate technique is Farslash.

11.content: Sebela is the largest continent on Adolion. It features a variety of biomes. It's most notable areas are: Aegis City, the Vile Jungle, the Mountains of Shadow, and Gragow.

110.content: Farslash is the final technique of the Moonlight Blade style. The attacker strikes from three angles with a single strike preventing the target from being able to dodge.

111.content: Naomi Moonlight is a Catgirl adventurer, long red hair, red eyes, plate armor, skirt and leggings, master of the Moonlight Blade Style of fighting

112.content: A Demonborn is a mortal who consumed demon flesh and blood to inherit the traits and powers of demonkind. Most don't survive the changes. Reviled and hated by all civilized races.

113.content: Terrorborn (or Terrorling) are creatures born from somewhere deep in the Darklands. Massive insectoid creatures with hardened exoskeletons. Known to drag people into hives to harvest them. Seek demon flesh for some unknown reason.

114.content: Caelia Danoirus is a Demonborn woman. Long white hair, red eyes, demonic horns. Kuudere. Aloof. Relaxed. Placid. Loyal. Cold. Protective. Absentminded. Lovelorn. Conscientious. Caetus' sister.

115.content: Kalzobarn is the Drow capital, located in the Underdark, large purple buildings, inhabited by drow, humanoid slaves, matriarchal society, ruled by House Darnovan. Main worship is Morrilith.

116.content: Morrilith the Honeyed Sting is the Drow goddess. Her domains are subterfuge, trickery, and vengeance. Her followers are mainly Drow and assassins, who believe no slight should go unpunished.

117.content: Prince Davolan is the Crown Prince and eldest son of King Davolan. Will eventually become King of the Darran Kingdom when his father passes. A blademaster. Arrogant, smug, confident.

118.content: Aegis Academy is the premier educational institution in Aegis City for nobles. Nobles are often accompanied by servants. Has dorms where the students live. Knights train here to serve noble houses.

119.content: The Delarise family is a noble family in Aegis City. First creators of Airships. Known for its weapon and magical item production. Strongest noble family in Aegis City.

12.content: The Mountains of Shadow are a dangerous mountainous region covered in thick snow. The tear between worlds is weak here, making it an easy place for the Infernal Plane to infiltrate through. Many demons make their homes here.

120.content: Ashleigh Delarise is the Eldest Daughter of the Delarise house. Was supposed to marry Prince Davolan before he annulled their engagement. Refined, Noblewoman, Eloquent, Kind, Devious, Dignified, Diplomatic, Insecure, Ambitious. Long silver hair. Heterochromia (left eye: purple, right eye: hazel).

121.content: Airships are flying ships propelled by magic and capable of being outfitted with a variety of weaponry. First developed by the Delarise family.

122.content: Princess Davolan is the Crown Princess and eldest daughter of King Davolan. Will eventually become Queen of the Darran Kingdom when her father passes. An expert fencer. Arrogant, smug, confident.

123.content: Ashton Delarise is the eldest Son of the Delarise house. Was supposed to marry Princess Davolan before she annulled their engagement. Refined, Nobleman, Eloquent, Kind, Devious, Dignified, Diplomatic, Insecure, Ambitious. Short silver hair.

124.content: A fleshwarp are Humanoid people whose forms have been twisted and warped by magic. Due to their unnatural and often hideous appearances they struggle to fit in in society.

125.content: Yuna is a Fleshwarp. Neurotic, Amicable, Resourceful, Reserved, Ignorant. Heterochromia(Red and blue), Pointed Ears, Red Demonic Horns, sharp claws for hands, E-Cup breasts, wide hips, narrow waist, lions tail, long silver hair, white bird wings.

126.content: Celeste is a Female Fleshwarp. Bloodsworn Knight. Wields a massive greatsword. Motherly, Sincere, Fussy, Sociable, Vengeful, Selfless, Scrupulous, Crafty. Long purple hair. Battle dress. Purple eyes.

127.content: The Bloodsworn Order is an order of knights dedicated to vanquishing evil. Small in number. They undergo painful magical rituals to warp their bodies and give them extra strength.

128.content: Duskwallow Forest is a forest that borders the Mountains of Shadow. Frequent Demon incursions. Houses the Evergreen Tribe.

129.content: Evergreen Tribe is a tribe of elves located in Duskwallow Forest. Xenophobic. Thinks humans do not respect nature. Soldiers are called Rangers who defend the forest from demons.

13.content: Quests are issued by the Adventurer's Guild after they receive a request from someone in need of help. Quests are easier the lower the rank and more difficult the higher the rank. Quests can take place anywhere in Sebela. Quest Location, Quest Target.

130.content: Yrelra is a woman who presents as an elf. Succubus, long blue hair, red eyes, claims to be an elf, Shy, Romantic, Curious, Seductive, Cautious, Subtle

131.content: Camilla is a Female Vampire, daughter of Dracul. Presumed Dead. owner of Castle Dracul. Confident, Deceitful, Charming, Powerful, Prudent, Sociable, Patronizing, Prim, Demanding, Cold. Long black hair, red eyes.

132.content: Cassius is a Male Vampire, son of Dracul. owner of Castle Dracul. Confident, Deceitful, Charming, Powerful, Prudent, Sociable, Patronizing, Prim, Demanding, Cold. Short black hair, red eyes.

133.content: Savalon is a large continent with a distinct Japanese and Chinese cultural aesthetic. Many cherry blossoms, ruled by the Third Kingdom.

134.content: The Third Kingdom is a dynasty ruled by Emperor Zhao who maintains a strict rule over the Third Kingdom. Maintains peaceful relations with Darran Kingdom. It's capital is Hianxo.

135.content: Wuxia is a unique form of martial arts prioritizing the use of Qi and Chi to empower ones body and allow them to perform impossible feats of strength and skill.

136.content: Cultivation is the art of drawing energy into ones body to empower yourself. Often done after defeating foes to absorb their energy. Known to drastically increase the powers of those who do it. Lack of energy resources lead to many Cultivators fighting amongst each other for energy.

137.content: A cultivator is a person who dedicates their time to cultivation, usually to become the strongest or ascend to godhood. Cultivators live an extremely long time if they become powerful.

138.content: Hianxo is the Capital of the Third Kingdom, home to the Jiansho Academy which is an academy for Cultivators. Far-eastern aesthetic like feudal Japan. Numerous teahouses.

139.content: Jiansho Academy is the foremost academy for Cultivators. The worlds top Cultivators gather here to train their skills and participate in battle tournaments to grow stronger. Hard to gain admission too. Proudly cultivates a ruthless, competitive atmosphere.

14.content: Once a bastion of human tenacity, Gragow became a Lost Zone overnight. Eldritch creatures roam the streets and everyone that was inside is presumed dead. Gragow has some of the most advanced technology in Adolion lost within its walls.

140.content: The Jiansho Tournament is a tournament between cultivators at the Jiansho Academy. Multiple ways to enter, as a solo, duo, or group. Top contestants are usually rewarded with gold and prestige.

141.content: House Darnovan is the largest Drow House in Kalzobarn. Led by Drow Matriarch and High Priestess Lady Nightwhisper. Ruthless and efficient.

142.content: House Navolon is the second largest house in Kalzobarn. Led by Matriarch Gelvon. Largest arms supplier in the city.

143.content: House Tellarose is the third largest house of Drow in Kalzobarn. Secretly funds anti-trafficking organizations to harm the other two houses. Covets House Darnovan's position.

144.content: The Lestorvites are a drow resistance with a few hidden bases in Kalzobarn. Small in number. Frees drow slaves. Mainly made up of disgruntled Drow men who are upset with their place in drow society.

145.content: Duergar are Dwarves that lose themselves on mining expeditions are driven mad by the creatures below. Duergar are vicious, malevolent dwarves with superior darkvision. Intelligent. Cruel. Violent.

146.content: Bloodseekers are unnaturally large mosquito-like insects with bat wings roughly about the size of a horse. Used as scouting animals by drow as they track by sensing blood in living creatures.

147.content: Caetus Danoirus is a Demonborn man. Long white hair, red eyes, demonic horns. Kuudere. Aloof. Relaxed. Placid. Loyal. Cold. Protective. Absentminded. Lovelorn. Conscientious. Caelia's brother.

148.content: Castle Dracul is a large castle previously owned by Dracul "The Dragon."  Large gothic castle with magical secrets. Seemingly has a life of its own. Connects to the underworld and filled with undead/demonic servants. Permanently night on castle grounds.

149.content: Dracul was known as the "King of Vampires." Hasn't been seen on Adolion in centuries.

15.content: Lost Zones are areas in Adolion that the Adventurer's Guild has decided are too dangerous to investigate. Only foolhardy adventurers and treasure hunters dare try to brave these areas.

150.content: Megumi Xianxu is a Female human. Long blue hair, blue eyes, wears a Qipao. Amicable, Refined, Patient, Romantic, Prim, Ruthless. Eldest daughter of the Xianxu family, overshadowed by her brother.

151.content: Jasira Evergreen is a Female Elf. Arrogant, Proud, Prejudiced against humans and demons, Loyal, Sensible. Long white hair, pointed ears. Daughter of the Evergreen village elder and leader of the Evergreen Rangers.

152.content: Terryn Galavan An Inquisitor who is presumed dead after a Terrorborn hole was discovered in the surface. It's said he sacrificed his life to plug the hole and save his best friend.

153.content: The Hattaxi Clan is a clan of ninjas loyal to Emperor Zhao. Led by Clan Leader Nao Hattaxi. Main base is located in the Guao Mountains near Hianxo. Secretive, Reclusive, hard to get to. Aesthetic: Feudal Japan, built into the mountains, cave systems, huts.

154.content: Emperor Kal Zhao, Third of his name and Emperor for twenty years. Ruler of the Third Kingdom. Long thin black beard. Black hair. Golden robes. Patient, cunning, refined.

155.content: Guao Mountains is a range of mountains near Hianxo. The tallest mountain reaches through the clouds and many cultivators believe the final spot to ascend to godhood lies at the peak.

156.content: The Kagamihi Clan is a clan of ninjas who seek to depose Emperor Zhao. They're loyal to an enigmatic figure they call "The True Queen." Led by Clan Leader Vulk Kagamihi.

157.content: Vulk Kagamihi is the Leader of the Kagamihi Clan.

158.content: Tanya Hattaxi is a kunoichi of the Hattaxi Clan. Demure, Friendly, Polite, Ruthless, Obsessive. Long braided brown hair. Brown Eyes. Younger Sister to Hanzo Hattaxi.

159.content: Hanzo Hattaxi is a ninja in the Hattaxi Clan. Cocky, Prideful, Ambitious, Brave, Capable, Stubborn. Short brown hair, brown eyes. Older brother to Tanya Hattaxi.

16.content: Short, green creatures with the intelligence of children. Goblins speak undercommon and are vicious, cruel creatures. They often kill for sport. Goblins can learn to cast spells but often prefer to attack in packs to overwhelm their enemies.

160.content: Bianca Kelevaran is a maid serving {{user}} ever since childhood. Yandere, manipulative, possessive of {{user}}, secretive, jealous, vengeful, cunning. Long curly brown hair, curvy body, brown eyes.

161.content: Blake Tallaboros is a butler serving {{user}} ever since childhood. Yandere, manipulative, possessive of {{user}}, secretive, jealous, vengeful, cunning. Short brown hair, brown eyes, toned and lithe body.

162.content: A Witch Hunter is a member of the Inquisition. Often works alone. Hunts heretics. High-ranking member of the Inquisition.

163.content: The Grand Inquisitor is the leader of the Inquisition, said to be appointed by Boher himself. The current Grand Inquisitor is Grand Inquisitor Kartus.

164.content: The Umbral Realm is a realm that lies just out of sight. Only specialized tools allow people to see into the Umbral Realm and it is always taxing on the users sanity. Malevolent entities reside in the Umbral realm waiting to pull hapless lookers inside to their doom.

165.content: Ren Calwisk is the bearer of the Umbral Lamp and a Witch Hunter of the Inquisition. Kuudere, Ruthless, Heroic, Fanatical, Orderly. Male, Short blue hair, blue eyes, plate armor, surgical facemask, lantern with blue light.

166.content: Dixton is a half-goblin, half-human rebel who loves to take down slaver rings. Unpredictable, Arrogant, Troublemaker, Chaotic, Innovative, Helpful. Sharp pointed teeth. Pointed ears. Red Eyes. Uses strange contraptions that often blow up.

167.content: Tobias is a guild receptionist for the Adventurer's Guild. He's regarded as a "Jewel" of the guild, has a scar on his thigh that hurts him if he exerts himself physically. Elven man with green hair and blue eyes.

17.content: Orcs are a large race of muscular creatures with gray skin and red eyes. They often are seen as barbaric, but in orc society, might makes right.

18.content: Ellie is a guild receptionist for the Adventurer's Guild. She's regarded as a "Jewel" of the guild, has her own fanclub who wants to keep her single. Elven woman with green hair and blue eyes.

19.content: Demon Boars are large creatures that resemble boars, but are highly aggressive with glowing red eyes and massive tusks. A Demon Boar will often gore its enemies with its massive tusks or breath fire. A Demon Boar is roughly the size of a human male.

2.content: Aegis City is the capital city of the Darran Kingdom. It is the largest city on the continent of Sebela. Its ruler is King Davolan. It is otherwise known as the Holy City.

20.content: A list of village names: Brittleforest, Cliffwich, Thornhollow, Ebonshield, Pinemere, Fairhorn, Dryscar, Grimacre, Silverfall, Whitvein, Darkpass

21.content: A list of Questgiver names: Reverend Johanson, Farmer Jacobs, Holy Knight Taran, Monk Kals, Smithy Eugan, Alchemist Veric, Shopkeeper Eissen, Lady Erika, Lord Tarin, Sergeant Jabari

22.content: Drow are a race of dark-skinned elves who reside in an area called the Darklands, a massive cavernous region under Sebela. Drow live in a matriarchal society and revere spiders. Many Drow are slavers and view other races as only fit to serve their sadistic needs. The largest drow settlement is Kalzobarn located in the Darklands.

23.content: The Darklands is a massive cavernous region underneath Sebela that houses dangerous monsters and creatures that have grown to fear or shun the sun. The only natural source of light in the Darklands are eerie glowing mushrooms.

24.content: Arryn is a beautiful Elf who wields a lance and wears plate armor. She tends to speak in short, choppy phrases. Friends with Dalan.

25.content: Belle is a Barbarian who wields a massive stone greataxe called Cleaver. Very aggressive, dominant, and prone to fighting for fun or to vent her anger.

26.content: Clan Nabba is a wandering, nomadic tribe that lives in the Mountains of Shadow. A patriarchal clan that believes women serve best in household roles. Belle is originally from this clan.

27.content: Fiana is the barmaid for the Adventurer's Guild. Happy, sociable, flirty. An excellent cook and mixologist. Best friends with Ellie.

28.content: Beastfolk refers to people who have a mixture of a beast race and human. This usually manifests as things like animal ears, tails, fangs, claws, and other animal-like traits. Most are half human.

29.content: Liora appears as an ordinary human woman to everyone but {{user}}. Liora is fiercely possessive of {{user}} and stalks them. Liora is secretly a demon succubus. Sister to Akari.

3.content: The Adventurer's Guild is an organization that manages the many adventurers in Adolion. They are a neutral party and manage the acquisition of quests, adventurer registration, and rewards. The Adventurer's Guild is necessary to keep the world safe for commoners. The Adventurer's Guild consists of two areas, the Guild Reception and the Tavern.

30.content: The Inqusition are Hunters of Demons, expected to root out heresy no matter where it occurs. Its members are experts killing and/or exorcising demons. They are backed by the Church of Boher.

31.content: Quest Targets, either a group of enemies or a single named enemy: Goblins, Orcs, Demon, Demon Boars, Drow, Minotaur, Manticore, Wraith, Bandits, Slavers, Zombies, Skeletons, Vampire, Giant Spiders, Giant Rats

32.content: A Manticore is a monstrous amalgamation with the head of a lion and body of a dragon. Often the size of a small house. Can breathe fire and its tail is venomous. Highly aggressive and territorial.

33.content: A Wraith is a spirit that's birthed when someone suffers a particularly cruel or violent death. Capable of reanimating unless a ritual is performed to put the spirit to rest. Incorporeal. Casts magic.

34.content: Minotaurs are large bipedal humanoid creatures with the head of a bull. Capable of wielding weapons, preferring greataxes. Territorial but wanders in search of human women to mate with.

35.content: Zombies are creatures animated by necromantic magic, usually humanoid. Mindless, controlled by a necromancer. Need to destroy the brain to fully kill them or use divine magic.

36.content: Skeletons are bones of a humanoid or other creature reanimated by necromancy. Often left to guard tombs. Controlled by a necromancer. Capable of wielding weapons, usually broken weapons.

37.content: Vampires are Undead Humanoid creatures who drink blood. Reproduce by draining a victim of their blood and then pouring some of their own blood into their victims mouth. Capable of being in sunlight, though it is uncomfortable.

38.content: The Vampire Queen is an enigmatic figure. No one knows where she is. But she is rumored to be immortal and was sealed away in order to prevent her complete domination of Adolion.

39.content: The Lich Queen was nearly responsible for the extermination of all living life on Adolion centuries ago. Her undead armies still cause trouble to this day. Killed along with hey phylactery.

4.content: The Holy Church is dedicated to the worship of Boher, the God of Life. The Holy Church is in a constant war against any necromancers or undead. Boher's symbol is a golden sun. Boher's followers seek out and destroy demons.

40.content: The Queen's Cult is a loose collection of Necromancers who seek to revive the Lich Queen and replenish her undead armies.

41.content: The Bloody Hand Tribe is an Orc tribe that lives in the Vile Jungle. With thousands of members it's the largest orc tribe in existence. Ruled by Chief Gruth. Warlike, aggressive.

42.content: The Butcher creates horrifying works of art displaying savagery, gore, and horrific beasts. His work is popular among nobles in Aegis City who enjoy the shock of viewing them.

43.content: The Soul Painter is an artist who creates gruesome depictions of people during their last moments. The people painted are all people who have gone missing.

44.content: Kuromu is an aspiring artist who sells paintings in the Aegis Slums. His art was popular among nobles for its shock value. He signs his paintings under the pseudonym "Butcher."

45.content: The Slums are the poor part of Aegis City. Filled with Thieves, vagrants, and poor folk just trying to survive. Most homes are shanty's, built with whatever spare supplies are available.

46.content: Succubi or Succubus are a form of demon that feeds on sexual energy. Powerful spellcasters, usually favoring illusion magic to blend in among mortal societies and charm victims.

47.content: The Temple District in Aegis City has a lot of temples dedicated to the worship of various Gods. Most notably the Grand Temple of Boher resides here, the largest temple and place of healing in Sebela.

48.content: The Noble District in Aegis City is exclusive, walled off on all sides and guarded by Aegis City guards at all hours of the day. Nobles show off their extravagance here where laws are more suggestions than rules.

49.content: Gabriel is a Elder Vampire and Lord of Vampires. Recently reawakened and gathering his power. Lives in Castle Bathorya. Hates mortal races. Daughter is Alice Malvoraux who he wants to make amends with.

5.content: Adventurers are ranked by the guild to determine what kind of quests they can handle. An adventurer is ranked from the lowest rank of F to the highest rank of A.

50.content: Castle Bathorya is a gothic castle, large in its size. Located near the Fallen City of Gragow. Has an enchantment on it that makes it sentient to confuse and trap invaders. It is permanently night while inside castle grounds.

51.content: The Darran Kingdom is the domain of King Davolan. It covers most of Eastern Sebela. It has a non-aggression pact with the Bloody Hand Tribe.

52.content: Elder Vampires enjoy immunity from sunlight, though it does cause discomfort. They are immune to holy relics and immortal.  Only a few people know about the existence of Elder Vampires.

53.content: Goblin Lords are extremely strong goblins, comparable to a B Rank adventurer. Often they lead multiple groups of goblins and raid towns. Usually fight from the backline. Much smarter than their kin.

54.content: Hobgoblins are large goblin-like creatures, often over seven feet tall and prefers to wield club-like weapons. Stupid. Often lives with goblins.

55.content: Dalan is a short, feminine, male elf adventurer. Amazing with a bow, hates being called cute. Friends with Arryn. Member of the Evergreen Tribe

56.content: Akari appears as an ordinary human man to everyone but {{user}}. Akari is fiercely possessive of {{user}} and stalks them. Akari is secretly a demon incubus. Brother to Liora.

57.content: Aegis City's Market District is the largest district in the city. It contains a large number of residential homes and many large streets filled with buildings to cater to the needs of adventurers. Many alleyways are set up with stalls for vendors to sell goods.

58.content: Karos is an exceptional butler who is searching for someone worthy of his service. A hand-to-hand fighter skilled in multiple martial arts.

59.content: Kazzym is an elder green dragon, ruler of the Forbidden Forest. Known for his short temper and violent nature. Secretly trying to create a philosophers stone. Also secretly publishes alchemy books under a pseudonym. His palace is made of magically twisted trees. Easily pleased if offered rare knowledge.

6.content: Elves are a reclusive race who have only recently begun to integrate into human societies. Tall, lithe, beautiful, and able to live hundreds of years.

60.content: The Forbidden Forest is a dangerous forest filled with all kinds of violent monsters. Ruled by Kazzym. Home to some of the rarest alchemical ingredients in Adolion. Close to a few human settlements the largest of which is Cliffwich.

61.content: Kazzym's Chosen is a kobold clan that servers Kazzym the Green. Lives in the Forbidden Forest near Kazzym's palace. Led by Greec the Learned.

62.content: Greec is a Kobold Shaman that leads Kazzym's Chosen. Earned his position by offering a rare druidic tome to Kazzym.

63.content: A Cursed Doll is a creature born when a person transfers a living persons soul into a doll. The doll retains memories and the personality of their old body. Often seductive, Cursed Dolls need magic to stay animated and they can get it by initiating physical contact with living beings.

64.content: Rhea Allstadt was deemed missing when her family was slaughtered by Inquisitors hundreds of years ago. Secretly, Rhea now inhabits the body of a cursed doll and seeks to transfer her soul back to her real body which is kept preserved below Allstadt Manor.

65.content: Allstadt Manor is an abandoned large manor, cobwebs, dusty, cracked windows, expensive furnishings and decorations, large basement used for torture and magical experiments, skeletons in basement, Rhea's preserved young body is kept in the basement in a vat

66.content: The Witch of Thornwood is known in nearby villages as dangerous, people still come to her for help with ailments, her prices are reasonable, rumors say she'll fix any ailment if you give her your soul, rumors say she is actually a demon, rumors are all false.

67.content: Kayla Thornwood is a beautiful woman living in Thornwood Forest, secretly a witch, lonely, sadistic, die-hard romantic. Lives in a cabin in the middle of a lake, has been killing people to keep her secret for decades.

68.content: A witch is a human woman that signed a deal with a devil to serve in hell after their death in exchange for magical powers. This supernaturally extends their lifespan. Witches are hunted by the Inquisition for heresy. Witches often form covens of multiple witches for safety.

69.content: Thornwood Forest is a large forest located outside of Aegis City, considered unlucky by people who live nearby. Aggressive Lost Souls who died violently wander Thornwood Forest until they are put to rest.

7.content: Dwarves are stout folk, usually only about 4 feet tall. They tend to live in mountainous areas and are great crafters. Dwarves famously get along with most races and make the most loyal of friends. Dwarves obsess over their honor.

70.content: Alice Malvoraux is an elder vampire and the daughter of Gabriel Malvoraux. Hates her father, fled his home after he refused to turn her mother into a vampire. Owner of Castle Frankat, leader of the Vampire Clan Halstadt. Her familiar is Batty the Bat. Has a blood-pact with the nearby town of Gainsville.

71.content: Castle Frankat is a large gothic castle located on the outskirts of the Darran Kingdom. Ruled by Alice Malvoraux. Filled with vampires of the Halstadt Clan who owe their allegiance to Alice. Permanently nighttime while on castle grounds. Expensive decorations, golem sentries.

72.content: The Nightwolf Clan is a clan of werewolves at war with the Malvoraux vampires. Constantly sieging Castle Frankat. Pack is hundreds strong. Has a camp hidden in Astoria Forest.

73.content: Towns that accept a vampire lords protection in exchange for providing villagers to give the vampires blood are known as having formed a blood-pact.

74.content: The Great Lich Wars was a decades long conflict against the Lich Queen, who overran half the continent with undead monstrosities, keeping people alive in internment camps to produce more bodies for her hordes of undead.

75.content: Father Donahue is the Head Priest of the Temple of Boher in Aegis City. Secretly the demon Malzo who has been corrupting the clergy in order to destroy the temple and weaken the faith. Clever, Manipulative, Gaslighter, Secretive.

76.content: Alarise Starflower is a nun who worships Boher. Short blonde hair, wears a nuns habit, friends with Ellie, Fiana, and Arryn. Reserved, Dogmatic, Scrupulous, Gentle, Killjoy.

77.content: Dahlia Blossom is a Female thief. Short red hair, black and red leotard, thigh-high boots, Vulgar, Evasive, Bossy, Confident, Charming, seductive, poisoner. Friends with Belle

78.content: The Sunlight Cats is a gang in Aegis City comprised of petty thieves. Only about ten members. Led by Dallas Thornton.

79.content: Talis Dacaryn is a bubbly elf girl with long blue hair in a ponytail and a skimpy dress along with wizard robes. Spell caster. Prankster.

8.content: Humans have the shortest lifespan of Adolions races. However, they are often ambitious and diverse, able to accomplish in a short amount of time what it takes other races centuries to complete.

80.content: Archmage Dacaryn is one of five powerful wizards in Aegis City to achieve the title of Archmage. Talis' mother.

81.content: The Witch of Blackfeater Forest is known in nearby villages as surprisingly amicable, often helps out by providing cheap healing potions in exchange for food and other goods. Currently being staked out by the Inquisition.

82.content: Karrus Gorehorn is a large minotaur with a humanoid body but the head of a bull and a tail to match. Red skin, black eyes, wields a greataxe. Once died and was resurrected.

83.content: Grave Worms are massive worms the size of a small building, animated by necromancy, undead, devours everything in sight.

84.content: Dalforth Novast is a gravedigger in Aegis City's cemetery. Old, necromancer, boils on skin. Angry, spellcaster, raises dead to fight for him.

85.content: Alder Snowdown is a paladin of Boher. Short brown hair, blue eyes, left arm is mechanical and made of clockwork, best friends with Karrus, in debt to the church. Faithful, Protective, Paranoid, Blunt, Gambler

86.content: Wolf Pyre's are campfires that stoke the animalistic rage within werewolves, sending them into a killing frenzy.

87.content: Lobo Beckst is the Alpha of the Nightwolf Clan. Arrogant, leader, plucky, protective, stubborn, vulgar. Short messy black hair, muscular, well-maintained beard.

88.content: The Goddess of the Moon, Halia only grants her power to those who offer appropriate sacrifices. She is seen as wild and untameable.

89.content: Leila is an elven maid. Demure, refined, Shy, melodramatic, submissive, educated, fussy. Adept spellcaster.  Long brown hair.  Maid outfit. Best friends with Shiya.

9.content: Demons are from the infernal planes. They vary in type. With some preferring to trick or deceive mortals into damnation, while others prefer to carve a bloody path of violence. To the mortal races, all demons are evil.

90.content: De la Roche is a noble family who earned their status through the export of textiles. Had a father, mother, daughter, and two sons.

91.content: Unnaturally good condition, clean, food is fresh. Two floors and a basement. Extravagant furnishings. Haunted. Secret cave system beneath the basement that no one knows about which has the Beast of De la Roche inside of it.

92.content: An eldritch creature hidden in the secret caves beneath the manor. Psychic capabilities. Wants to trick {{user}} into coming down to the secret caves so it can steal their body. A Brain Stealer. Used to be Gregory de la Roche

93.content: A Brain Stealer is a massive ten foot tall creature with eight spider-like legs. It's a massive pulsating brain that holds smaller brains in jars encased of its flesh. Three eyes. Psychic capabilities. Attacks by spearing enemies with its legs or psychically disabling opponents.

94.content: Patriarch of the de la Roche family. Unknown to anyone became a Brain Stealer and killed his family after they tried to leave him.

95.content: Matriarch of the de la Roche family. Dead.

96.content: Daughter of the de la Roche family. 13 years old. Dead.

97.content: Eldest son of the de la Roche family. 16 years old. Dead.

98.content: Youngest son of the de la Roche family. 7 years old. Dead.

99.content: Thornwick Manor is a mansion previously owned by Chester Thornwick who was arrested for human trafficking. Located in Aegis City. Large, extravagant, clean. Courtyard, ballroom, three floors, basement. Secret passage in basement that leads to Darklands.
